Which of the following commands shows the usage of inodes across all filesystems?
A)  df - i
B)  ls - i
C)  du - i
D)  dm - i
A
A. The - i option to df produces information on inodes across all filesystems. Thels - i option will produce inode listings but only for the current directory. The - i optionis invalid for du, and dm does not exist as a command.
